# Exclude lsp clj.kondo and calva
.lsp/
.clj-kondo/
.calva/
 
 This is the  .gitignore  file that I use for my Clojure projects. It is a combination of the default  .gitignore  file for Clojure and some additional exclusions for the  lsp ,  clj-kondo , and  calva  directories. 
 The  .lsp/  directory is created by the  lsp  plugin for VS Code. The  .clj-kondo/  directory is created by the  clj-kondo  plugin for VS Code. The  .calva/  directory is created by the  calva  plugin for VS Code. 
 By excluding these directories from the Git repository, you can avoid committing unnecessary files to the repository. 
 How to create a .gitignore file 
 To create a  .gitignore  file, you can use any text editor. Here is how you can create a  .gitignore  file using the  touch  command in the terminal: 
 touch .gitignore
 
 This will create an empty  .gitignore  file in the current directory. You can then open the file in a text editor and add the necessary entries to exclude files and directories from the Git repository. 
 How to add a .gitignore file to a Git repository 
 To add a  .gitignore  file to a Git repository, you can simply create the file in the root directory of the repository and commit it to the repository. Here is how you can add a  .gitignore  file to a Git repository: 
 touch .gitignore